data.title: Austin Public Library
data.text:
Expand a section below for answers to frequently asked questions.

What you need to apply

What you need to apply link

Personal check or money order payable to the U.S. Department of State. A separate check or money order for each application is preferred. The US Department of State does not accept temporary or business checks.

Completed form DS-11 Passport Application, unsigned and filled out in black ink or typed. Available at travel.state.gov/applyinperson. Please print single-sided. Please note, we do not accept Form DS-82.

Color passport photo 2x2 inches in size. For photo requirements, see travel.state.gov/photos. Required photos may also be taken during your appointment at the Austin Public Library Passport Services Office.

Valid, unexpired photo ID plus single-sided front-and-back photocopy. If out-of-state, a supplementary ID document is needed. See travel.state.gov/identification for a list of acceptable ID documents.

Evidence of U.S. Citizenship plus photocopy. Examples include a long-form U.S. birth certificate, certificate of naturalization, or prior full-validity U.S. passport. For details, see travel.state.gov/citizenship. Note: you must provide the original or a certified copy from the office of record. This will be submitted with your application and returned to you by mail.

Documentation of name changes or other names used. Original or certified copy required.

Passport Fees

Passport Fees link

Two separate payments are required:

A personal check or money order payable to the U.S. Department of State, per application (Passport application fees). The US Department of State does not accept temporary or business checks.

A credit or debit card, or check or money order for the Acceptance Facility fee, per application.

Acceptance fees are set by federal regulation. By law, passport fees are non-refundable.

Application Fees for a Passport Book by Personal Check or Money Order

A passport book may be used for international travel by air, land or sea.

$130 for an applicant aged 16 or older

$100 for an applicant aged 15 or younger

Expedited Processing: add $60 per application

1-2 day shipping of passport book to you: add $21.36 per application

Payable to the U.S. Department of State by personal check or money order ONLY. The US Department of State does not accept temporary or business checks.

Application Fees for a Passport Card by Personal Check or Money Order

A passport card may be used only for border crossings by land or sea in the United States, Canada, Mexico, the Caribbean, and Bermuda. It cannot be used for international travel by air.

$30 for an applicant aged 16 or older

$15 for an applicant aged 15 or younger

Payable to the U.S. Department of State by personal check or money order ONLY. The US Department of State does not accept temporary or business checks. Can be combined with payment for a passport book.

Acceptance Facility-Library Fees by Personal Check, Money Order, or Credit or Debit Card

Application acceptance fee: $35

Photo services fee: $12

Payable to Austin Public Library by credit or debit card, check or money order. No cash, please.

Processing Times

Processing Times link

Subject to change. Please see the U.S. Department of State for Processing Times details.

Routine Service: 6-8 weeks

Expedited: 2-3 weeks

Passport Renewals

Passport Renewals link

If your previous passport was issued when you were 16 or older or has been expired for less then five years (fifteen years from the issue date), you may be eligible to renew by mail. If you choose to renew in person, you must complete the DS-11 Passport Application and pay the $35 application acceptance fee. We cannot accept the DS-82 Renewal Application. See travel.state.gov/renew for more details.
